ssary_content','A book or an electronic resource to which one can refer for information and authoritative facts. Reference works are usually referred to for particular pieces of information, and the information is compiled for ease of reference, e.g. by using indices. Examples include encyclopedias, dictionaries, manuals, lexica, thesauri, catalogues, bibliographies, atlases, glossaries, handbooks.'),(3421,161,'_oes_demo_glossary_content','oes_demo_glossary_content'),(3422,161,'oes_demo_glossary_source',''),(3423,161,'_oes_demo_glossary_source','oes_demo_glossary_source'),(3424,162,'_edit_lock','1612452776:4'),(3425,162,'_edit_last','4'),(3426,162,'oes_demo_glossary_title','Lexicon'),(3427,162,'_oes_demo_glossary_title','oes_demo_glossary_title'),(3428,162,'oes_demo_glossary_author','a:1:{i:0;s:3:\"157\";}'),(3429,162,'_oes_demo_glossary_author','oes_demo_glossary_author'),(3430,162,'oes_editing_status','published'),(3431,162,'_oes_editing_status','oes_editing_status'),(3432,162,'oes_demo_glossary_publication_date','20201116'),(3433,162,'_oes_demo_glossary_publication_date','oes_demo_glossary_publication_date'),(3434,162,'oes_demo_glossary_latest_change',''),(3435,162,'_oes_demo_glossary_latest_change','oes_demo_glossary_latest_change'),(3436,162,'oes_demo_glossary_content','A book containing (a list of) the words in a language (and their definitions) in alphabetical order. The word <i>lexicon</i> derives from the Greek <span lang=\"grc\" title=\"Ancient Greek language text\">λεξικόν</span> (<i lang=\"grc-Latn\" title=\"Ancient Greek language text\">lexikon</i>), neuter of <span lang=\"grc\" title=\"Ancient Greek language text\">λεξικός</span> (<i lang=\"grc-Latn\" title=\"Ancient Greek language text\">lexikos</i>) meaning \'of or for words\'.'),(3437,162,'_oes_demo_glossary_content','oes_demo_glossary_content'),(3438,162,'oes_demo_glossary_source',''),(3439,162,'_oes_demo_glossary_source','oes_demo_glossary_source'),(3440,163,'_edit_lock','1608022126:1'),(3441,163,'_edit_last','1'),(3442,163,'oes_demo_article_master_title','Brockhaus Encyclopedia'),(3443,163,'_oes_demo_article_master_title','oes_demo_article_master_title'),(3444,163,'oes_demo_article_index_person','a:3:{i:0;s:3:\"209\";i:1;s:3:\"211\";i:2;s:3:\"210\";}'),(3445,163,'_oes_demo_article_index_person','oes_demo_article_index_person'),(3446,163,'oes_demo_article_index_place','a:4:{i:0;s:3:\"180\";i:1;s:3:\"182\";i:2;s:3:\"184\";i:3;s:3:\"183\";}'),(3447,163,'_oes_demo_article_index_place','oes_demo_article_index_place'),(3448,163,'oes_demo_article_index_subject','a:2:{i:0;s:3:\"208\";i:1;s:3:\"227\";}'),(3449,163,'_oes_demo_article_index_subject','oes_demo_article_index_subject'),(3450,163,'oes_demo_article_index_time','a:4:{i:0;s:3:\"193\";i:1;s:3:\"188\";i:2;s:3:\"197\";i:3;s:3:\"194\";}'),(3451,163,'_oes_demo_article_index_time','oes_demo_article_index_time'),(3452,164,'oes_version_master_id','163'),(3453,164,'oes_demo_article_excerpt','The Brockhaus Enzyklopädie (Encyclopedia) is the most famous reference work in German language and was published by the publishing house F.A. Brockhaus until 2009. After more than 200 years, distribution of the Brockhaus Enzyklopädie was discontinued in 2014, since when it has been published exclusively as online-edition.'),(3454,164,'_oes_demo_article_excerpt','oes_demo_article_excerpt'),(3455,164,'oes_demo_article_title','Brockhaus Enzyklopädie'),(3456,164,'_oes_demo_article_title','oes_demo_article_title'),(3457,164,'oes_editing_status','published'),(3458,164,'_oes_editing_status','oes_editing_status'),(3459,164,'oes_demo_article_pub_date','20201123'),(3460,164,'_oes_demo_article_pub_date','oes_demo_article_pub_date'),(3461,164,'oes_demo_article_latest_change','20210111'),(3462,164,'_oes_demo_article_latest_change','oes_demo_article_latest_change'),(3463,164,'oes_post_version','1.0'),(3464,164,'_oes_post_version','oes_post_version'),(3465,164,'oes_demo_article_doi_system',''),(3466,164,'_oes_demo_article_doi_system','oes_demo_article_doi_system'),(3467,164,'oes_demo_article_content','<hr />\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> The sole purpose of this article is to illustrate the functioning of Open Encyclopedia System. There is no claim to completeness or correctness.</em>\r\n\r\nThe <em>Brockhaus Enzyklopädie</em> (Brockhaus Encyclopedia) is the most famous <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/oes_demo_glossary/reference-work/\">reference work</a> in German language and was published by the publishing house F.A. Brockhaus until 2009. After more than 200 years, distribution of the <em>Brockhaus Enzyklopädie</em> was discontinued in 2014, since when it has been published exclusively as an online edition.[oes_note]<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brockhaus_Enzyklop%C3%A4die\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brockhaus_Enzyklop%C3%A4die </a>[23.11.2020][/oes_note]\r\n<h1>History</h1>\r\nThe predecessor of the <em>Brockhaus Enzyklopädie</em> was the <em>Conversations-Lexicon </em>(Conversational Lexicon), which first appeared in the 18th century. This <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/oes_demo_glossary/encyclopedia/\">encyclopedia</a>, published since 1796 by the <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_place=leipzig\">Leipzig</a> scholars <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_person=lobel-renatus-gotthelf\">Renatus Gotthelf Löbel</a> (1767-1799) and <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_person=franke-christian-wilhelm\">Christian Wilhelm Franke</a> (1765-1831), contained articles on geography, history, philosophy, mythology, natural history, etc.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_person=brockhaus-friedrich-arnold\">Friedrich Arnold Brockhaus</a> (1772-1823) bought the publishing rights for the <em>Conversations-Lexicon</em> for 1800 thalers at the Leipzig book fair in 1808. The foundation of <em>Brockhaus</em>\' success was laid with the 2nd edition, which was published Easter 1812 under the title <em>Conversations-Lexicon oder enzyklopädisches Handwörterbuch für gebildete Stände</em>, comprising eight volumes. During the 19th century 13 editions were published. The articles, most of which were concise, were considered to be excellently researched and trustworthy.\r\n\r\nLater the name <em>Der Große Brockhaus</em> (The Great Brockhaus) was used for the encyclopedia, and since the 17th edition in 1966 the name <em>Brockhaus Enzyklopädie</em> has become established. Until 2009, the <em>Brockhaus Enzyklopädie</em> was published by F. A. Brockhaus or the Mannheim-based publishing house Bibliographisches Institut &amp; F. A. Brockhaus AG. In 2013 it was announced that the encyclopedia would only be published online,[oes_note]<a href=\"http://www.spiegel.de/kultur/literatur/bertelsmann-gibt-brockhaus-auf-a-905187.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ende einer Ära: Brockhaus-Lexika droht das Aus.</a> <a href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spiegel_Online\">Spiegel Online</a>, Spiegel Online, 11. Juni 2013[07.12.2020][/oes_note][oes_note]H. Spiegel (2013)[/oes_note] and in 2014 the distribution of the printed edition was discontinued.[oes_note]A. Kramer (2017)[/oes_note] Since 2015 the online edition of the <em>Brockhaus Enzyklopädie</em> has been developed and marketed by NE GmbH (Sweden).\r\n<h1>Editions and volumes</h1>\r\nWhile the 2nd edition of 1812 was still in eight volumes, the 14th edition of 1894 already consisted of 16 regular volumes and one supplement volume, featuring 18,842 pages. Preparations for the 15th edition were disrupted by World War I, but were continued during the Weimar Republic. The 15th edition was finally published in 1934, featuring 20 volumes (15,800 pages), and a supplement volume published in 1935. The 21st edition (2005-2006) of the <em>Brockhaus Enzyklopädie</em>, the latest full print version, contains about 300,000 entries on about 24,000 pages, with about 40,000 maps, graphics and tables. It is the largest German-language printed encyclopedia in the 21st century. Over the years, several abbreviated editions have been published in addition to the full encyclopedia, such as the <em>Kleineres Brockhaus\'sches Conversations-Lexikon für den Hausgebrauch</em> (Minor Brockhaus Encyclopedia for Home Use)  in 1854 (4 volumes) or <em>Der Volks-Brockhaus</em> (The People\'s Brockhaus), the first single-volume version, first published in 1931 (1040 pages in the 15th edition in 1975).'),(3468,164,'_oes_demo_article_content','oes_demo_article_content'),(3469,164,'oes_demo_article_content_source',''),(3470,164,'_oes_demo_article_content_source','oes_demo_article_content_source'),(3471,164,'oes_demo_article_citation_style','Adele Author. Brockhaus Encyclopedia. In: OES Demo. Published by Center for Digital Systems, Freie Universität Berlin, Berlin, 23.11.2020.'),(3472,164,'_oes_demo_article_citation_style','oes_demo_article_citation_style'),(3473,164,'oes_demo_article_licence_type','https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/'),(3474,164,'_oes_demo_article_licence_type','oes_demo_article_licence_type'),(3475,164,'oes_demo_article_media_file',''),(3476,164,'_oes_demo_article_media_file','oes_demo_article_media_file'),(3477,164,'oes_demo_article_media_gallery','521'),(3478,164,'_oes_demo_article_media_gallery','oes_demo_article_media_gallery'),(3479,164,'oes_demo_article_media_link_1','https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brockhaus_Enzyklop%C3%A4die'),(3480,164,'_oes_demo_article_media_link_1','oes_demo_article_media_link_1'),(3481,164,'oes_demo_article_media_link_2','https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brockhaus_Enzyklop%C3%A4die'),(3482,164,'_oes_demo_article_media_link_2','oes_demo_article_media_link_2'),(3483,164,'oes_demo_article_media_link_3',''),(3484,164,'_oes_demo_article_media_link_3','oes_demo_article_media_link_3'),(3485,164,'oes_demo_article_media_link_4',''),(3486,164,'_oes_demo_article_media_link_4','oes_demo_article_media_link_4'),(348