ent','<h1>A short introduction</h1>\r\nThe <em>Compendium heroicum</em> reflects the current state of research on heroes and heroines and features detailed illustrations on various phenomena of the heroic, its figures, functions, mediality and practice. Methodologically, the <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/wordpress/oes_demo_glossary/compendium/\">Compendium</a> heroicum applies a broad historical approach – ranging from the ancient world to the present day – as well as a cross-cultural perspective, focusing on the importance of heroic figures within and beyond European contexts. Researchers at the <a href=\"https://www.sfb948.uni-freiburg.de/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Collaborative Research Center 948</a> as well as external contributors author collaboratively written articles to be published on the \"Compendium heroicum\". All articles will be digitally accessible worldwide free of charge (Open Access).'),(4876,245,'_oes_demo_article_content','oes_demo_article_content'),(4877,245,'oes_demo_article_citation_style',''),(4878,245,'_oes_demo_article_citation_style','oes_demo_article_citation_style'),(4879,245,'oes_demo_article_media_gallery',''),(4880,245,'_oes_demo_article_media_gallery','oes_demo_article_media_gallery'),(4881,245,'_edit_lock','1611932491:4'),(4882,245,'_edit_last','4'),(4883,244,'oes_version_children_ids','a:1:{i:0;i:245;}'),(4885,245,'oes_demo_article_author',''),(4886,245,'_oes_demo_article_author','oes_demo_article_author'),(4887,245,'oes_demo_article_further_contributors',''),(4888,245,'_oes_demo_article_further_contributors','oes_demo_article_further_contributors'),(4889,245,'oes_demo_article_biblio','a:1:{i:0;s:3:\"316\";}'),(4890,245,'_oes_demo_article_biblio','oes_demo_article_biblio'),(4891,245,'oes_demo_article_glossary','a:1:{i:0;s:3:\"156\";}'),(4892,245,'_oes_demo_article_glossary','oes_demo_article_glossary'),(4893,245,'oes_demo_article_article',''),(4894,245,'_oes_demo_article_article','oes_demo_article_artic