'_oes_demo_bibliography_glossary','oes_demo_bibliography_glossary'),(5433,275,'_edit_lock','1610531001:1'),(5434,275,'_edit_last','1'),(5435,275,'oes_demo_article_master_title','Duden Wörterbuch'),(5436,275,'_oes_demo_article_master_title','oes_demo_article_master_title'),(5437,276,'oes_version_master_id','275'),(5438,276,'oes_demo_article_title','Duden Wörterbuch'),(5439,276,'oes_editing_status','published'),(5440,276,'_oes_editing_status','oes_editing_status'),(5441,276,'oes_demo_article_excerpt','The Duden is a dictionary of the German language, and has long been the prescriptive source of German regarding grammar and spelling. It was first published by Konrad Duden in 1880, with regular updates every four or five years. The current edition published in 2020 is the 28th. The Duden dictionary is also available online. '),(5442,276,'_oes_demo_article_excerpt','oes_demo_article_excerpt'),(5443,276,'_oes_demo_article_title','oes_demo_article_title'),(5444,276,'oes_demo_article_pub_date','20201130'),(5445,276,'_oes_demo_article_pub_date','oes_demo_article_pub_date'),(5446,276,'oes_demo_article_latest_change','20210112'),(5447,276,'_oes_demo_article_latest_change','oes_demo_article_latest_change'),(5448,276,'oes_post_version','1.0'),(5449,276,'_oes_post_version','oes_post_version'),(5450,276,'oes_demo_article_licence_type','https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/'),(5451,276,'_oes_demo_article_licence_type','oes_demo_article_licence_type'),(5452,276,'oes_demo_article_doi_system',''),(5453,276,'_oes_demo_article_doi_system','oes_demo_article_doi_system'),(5454,276,'oes_demo_article_content','<em>Disclaimer: The sole purpose of this article is to illustrate the functioning of OES. There is no claim to completeness or correctness.</em>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The <em>Duden</em> is a <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_demo_glossary=dictionary\">dictionary</a> of the German language, and has long been the prescriptive source of German regarding grammar and spelling. It was first published by <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_person=duden-konrad\">Konrad Duden</a> in 1880, with regular updates every four or five years. The current edition published in 2020 is the 28<sup>th.</sup> In the 20th century, the <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_institute=duden-verlag\">Duden Verlag</a> (Duden publishing house) (<a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_place=mannheim\">Mannheim</a>, then <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_place=berlin\">Berlin</a>) developed a series with further specialized dictionaries as well as a grammar, which also appeared under the title <em>Duden</em>.[oes_note]<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duden\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duden</a> [16.12.2020][/oes_note] The <em>Duden</em> dictionary is also available online.[oes_note]Duden Wörterbuch Online: <a href=\"https://www.duden.de/woerterbuch\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://www.duden.de/woerterbuch [</a>16.12.2020][/oes_note]</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>History</strong></h1>\r\nIn 1872 <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_person=duden-konrad\">Konrad Duden</a> published his treatise <em>Die deutsche Rechtschreibung</em> (The German Orthography), which became the basis for the following orthographic dictionaries. Eight years later, the first edition of his main work, the <em>Vollständige Orthographische Wörterbuch der deutschen Sprache</em> (Complete Orthographical Dictionary of the German Language[oes_note]Stang (2013)[/oes_note], was published by the <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_institute=bibliographisches-institut-leipzig\">Bibliographisches Institut</a> (Bibliographical Institute) in <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_place=leipzig\">Leipzig</a>. This first <em>Duden</em> collected 27,000 keywords on 187 pages, and was declared the official source for correct spelling in the administration of <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_place=prussia\">Prussia</a>. In 1902 the <em>Duden</em> was confirmed as the official standard for German spelling and continued to be the <em>de facto</em> standard for the next decade.\r\n\r\nAfter World War II and as consequence of the German division, the Duden tradition continued separately in East Germany (1951, <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_place=leipzig\">Leipzig</a>) and West Germany (1954, <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_place=mannheim\">Mannheim</a>). The main differences between the two versions of <em>Duden</em> appear in the number of entries (<em>Stichwörter</em>), with a diminishing number of entries in the East German <em>Duden</em> as compared to an increasing number in the West German edition, and in the type of lexical entries. Socialist-influenced terms and loan words from Russian were found in the G.D.R. Duden, and new West German everyday terms and loan words from English were added to the F.R.G. Duden. As late as the 1960s, the Leipzig <em>Duden</em> editorial office, which sees itself in a historical tradition, tried to publish a dictionary that was as apolitical as possible in order to prevent a division of spelling in Germany.[oes_note]<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duden\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duden</a> [16.12.2020][/oes_note] In the 1950s, some publishing houses in West Germany questioned the <em>Duden</em> monopoly, but in 1955 the ministers of culture of the states of Germany confirmed the spellings given by the <em>Duden</em> would continue to be the official standard.[oes_note]<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duden\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duden</a> [16.12.2020][/oes_note] Printing continued in both Mannheim and Leipzig until the German reunification in 1990.\r\n<h1>Duden today</h1>\r\nThe 20th edition of the <em>Duden</em> (August 1991) is known as <em>Einheitsduden</em> because it reunited the two German Duden. The publishing group <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_institute=bibliographisches-institut-f-a-brockhaus-ag\">Bibliographisches Institut &amp; F. A. Brockhaus AG</a> had taken over the <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/?oes_index_institute=bibliographisches-institut-leipzig\">Bibliographisches Institut Leipzig</a>. This Duden was the last edition before the spelling reform of 1996. On May 2, 2011 <em>Duden online</em> was launched as a free service. In 2019, the online offer contains over 236,000 entries [oes_note]Duden Wörterbuch Online: <a href=\"https://www.duden.de/woerterbuch\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://www.duden.de/woerterbuch</a> [16.12.2020][/oes_note]'),(5455,276,'_oes_demo_article_content','oes_demo_article_content'),(5456,276,'oes_demo_article_citation_style','Arthur Author. Duden Wörterbuch. In: OES Demo. Published by Center for Digital Systems, Freie Universität Berlin, Berlin, 30.11.2020.'),(5457,276,'_oes_demo_article_citation_style','oes_demo_article_citation_style'),(5458,276,'oes_demo_article_media_gallery','523'),(5459,276,'_oes_demo_article_media_gallery','oes_demo_article_media_gallery'),(5460,276,'_edit_lock','1612374367:4'),(5461,276,'_edit_last','4'),(5462,276,'oes_demo_article_author',''),(5463,276,'_oes_demo_article_author','oes_demo_article_author'),(5464,276,'oes_demo_article_further_contributors','a:1:{i:0;s:3:\"279\";}'),(5465,276,'_oes_demo_article_further_contributors','oes_demo_article_further_contributors'),(5466,276,'oes_demo_article_biblio','a:5:{i:0;s:3:\"274\";i:1;s:3:\"272\";i:2;s:3:\"273\";i:3;s:3:\"405\";i:4;s:3:\"406\";}'),(5467,276,'_oes_demo_article_biblio','oes_demo_article_biblio'),(5468,276,'oes_demo_article_glossary','a:2:{i:0;s:3:\"158\";i:1;s:3:\"161\";}'),(5469,276,'_oes_demo_article_glossary','oes_demo_