steps are:<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><span style=\"color: #ff9900;\"> </span>\r\n</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Remove the OES Demo data from the data base</li>\r\n 	<li>Customise the data model using the configuration options inside the editorial layer or edit the data model via configuration files inside the OES Demo sources.</li>\r\n 	<li>Tailor your website by adjusting the OES Demo theme via the configuration options inside the editorial layer or by editing the OES Demo theme sources.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and/or import your own data.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIf you intend to make major changes to the data model or the website theme you will have to edit the OES Demo sources. This requires knowledge about WordPress plugins and themes including programming skills in php and javaScript.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"acknowledgement\" class=\"content-table-header1\">Acknowledgement</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The Open Encyclopedia System Software and the OES Demo application have been developed at the Center for Digital Systems, Freie Universität Berlin. The development of the Open Encyclopedia System Software (<a href=\"https://www.open-encyclopedia-system.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.open-encyclopedia-system.org</a>) was funded by the German Research Foundation (DFG) from 2016-2020 as part of the project \"From 1914-1918-online to the Open Encyclopedia System\" (see <a href=\"https://gepris.dfg.de/gepris/projekt/195110440?language=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">GEPRIS entry</a>).</div>','About OES DEMO','','inherit','closed','closed','','465-revision-v1','','','2021-02-04 14:13:09','2021-02-04 13:13:09','',465,'http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/465-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(581,4,'2021-02-04 14:14:40','2021-02-04 13:14:40','The OES Demo application (OES Demo) provides an exemplary online encyclopedia that allows you to experience the frontend and editorial layer of an exemplary application. OES Demo includes a basic online encyclopedia administered by the WordPress admin dashboard and displayed by a WordPress theme.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Please note that the content of the OES demo encylopedia was created merely for demonstrational purposes, it makes no claim of being correct and complete. For exploring \"real content\", visit the academic online encyclopedias that have already been created using the OES framework at <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/oes_demo_article/?category=2-oes-use-cases\">OES use cases</a>.</em>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n<div class=\"content-table-header1\">Table of Content</div>\r\n-->\r\n<ul id=\"table-of-content\">\r\n 	<li id=\"header1\"><a href=\"#get\"><i class=\"fa fa fa-chevron-right\"></i> Get to know the OES Demo application</a></li>\r\n 	<li id=\"header1\"><a href=\"#explore\"><i class=\"fa fa fa-chevron-right\"></i> Explore the OES Demo in depth</a></li>\r\n 	<li id=\"header1\"><a href=\"#create\"><i class=\"fa fa fa-chevron-right\"></i> Create your own OES Demo-based online reference work</a></li>\r\n 	<li id=\"header1\"><a href=\"#acknowledgement\"><i class=\"fa fa fa-chevron-right\"></i> Acknowledgement</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"get\" class=\"content-table-header1\">Get to know the OES Demo application</div>\r\nThe OES Demo application consists of the WordPress admin dashboard, where users with specific rights can create, edit and manage content or configure the application (the \"<strong>editorial layer</strong>\"), a <strong>data model</strong> that is part of the OES Demo plugin sources and a WordPress theme which is the web template system for this public website (the \"<strong>frontend</strong>\").\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"get\" class=\"content-table-header2\">Data Model</div>\r\nFor this online encyclopedia the data model consists of different post types. The main post type is an <strong>article</strong>. An article holds the actual article content and additional information such as the title, publication date, DOI, etc. It can be connected to other post types such as <strong>contributors</strong>. A contributor consists of information about a contributing person such as name, contact information and authority files. A contributor can be an author of an article or an additional contributor (e.g. translator) to an article. Further post types are: <strong>glossary entries</strong>, <strong>bibliographic entries</strong> and multiple <strong>index entries</strong>, which can all be connected to articles and partly connected among themselves. The data model includes also taxonomies which can group and enrich post types, e.g. the taxonomy \'Categories\' groups articles into \'Reference Works\' and \'OES Use Cases\' and the taxonomy \'Author Keywords\' adds tags to articles. The OES feature \"Versioning\" enables different versions of an article that are grouped and organised by a post type <strong>master article</strong>.\r\n<figure><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/oes_demo_datamodel.jpg\" alt=\"Data Model\" /><figcaption><i>Figure 1: Data Model</i></figcaption></figure>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"get\" class=\"content-table-header2\">Editorial Layer</div>\r\nYou can access the editorial layer to explore the data model and configuration options <a href=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/wp-admin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here</a> or via the \"Login to Backend\" button in the footer below. Please send a mail to info@open-encyclopedia-system.org to obtain access to the backend. Note that this is a read only access, i.e. you cannot add, modify or delete any data or configurations.\r\n<figure><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/editing_layer.png\" alt=\"Editorial Layer\" /><figcaption><i>Figure 2: Editorial Layer</i></figcaption></figure>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"explore\" class=\"content-table-header1\">Explore the OES Demo in depth</div>\r\nOES is a WordPress plugin, developed on WordPress version 5.4.2. A typical OES application consists of the OES Core plugin and an additional OES Project plugin which implements the OES features for the application and a WordPress Theme to create the frontend. Hence, in order to explore the OES Demo framework in depth (add content, modify data model and set configuration options), you need to download the OES Core plugin and the OES Demo project plugin and install it locally.\r\n\r\nYou can download the current stable version of the OES Core plugin at <a href=\"https://github.com/open-encyclopedia-system/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/open-encyclopedia-system/</a>. The OES Demo plugin can be found at <a href=\"https://github.com/open-encyclopedia-system/oes-demo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/open-encyclopedia-system/oes-demo</a> and the OES Demo Wordpress theme at <a href=\"https://github.com/open-encyclopedia-system/oes-demo-theme\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/open-encyclopedia-system/oes-demo-theme</a>. The sources include an installation guide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"create\" class=\"content-table-header1\">Create your own OES Demo-based online reference work</div>\r\nOnce you have downloaded the OES software (see above) and have made yourself familiar with the data model and the configuration options you can create your own online reference work. You can use the OES Demo as a starting point and tailor it to your needs. Recommended steps are:<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><span style=\"color: #ff9900;\"> </span>\r\n</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Remove the OES Demo data from the data base</li>\r\n 	<li>Customise the data model using the configuration options inside the editorial layer or edit the data model via configuration files inside the OES Demo sources.</li>\r\n 	<li>Tailor your website by adjusting the OES Demo theme via the configuration options inside the editorial layer or by editing the OES Demo theme sources.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and/or import your own data.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIf you intend to make major changes to the data model or the website theme you will have to edit the OES Demo sources. This requires knowledge about WordPress plugins and themes including programming skills in php and javaScript.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"acknowledgement\" class=\"content-table-header1\">Acknowledgement</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The Open Encyclopedia System (OES) Software and the OES Demo application are being developed at the Center for Digital Systems, Freie Universität Berlin. The development of the OES Software (<a href=\"https://www.open-encyclopedia-system.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.open-encyclopedia-system.org</a>) was funded by the German Research Foundation (DFG) from 2016-2020 as part of the project \"From 1914-1918-online to the Open Encyclopedia System\" (see <a href=\"https://gepris.dfg.de/gepris/projekt/195110440?language=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">GEPRIS entry</a>).</div>','About OES DEMO','','inherit','closed','closed','','465-revision-v1','','','2021-02-04 14:14:40','2021-02-04 13:14:40','',465,'http://oes01.cedis.fu-berlin.de:8082/465-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(582,4,'2021-02-04 14:17:27','2021-02-04 13:17:27','The OES Demo application (OES Demo) provides an exemplary online encyclopedia that allows you to experience the frontend and editorial layer of an exemplary application. OES Demo includes a basic online encyclopedia administered by the WordPress admin dashboard and displayed by a WordPress theme.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Please note that the content of the OES demo encylopedia was created merely for demonstrational purposes, it makes no claim of being correct and complete. For exploring \"real content\", visit the academic online encyclop